question.title: How to handle a SSLSocketImpl Deadlock properly?

node.contents: The real question here is why are you letting an SSLSocket be garbage-collected?

astNode.text: The real question here is why are you letting an SSLSocket be garbage-collected?

node.contents: An update to Java 8 did the fix, it seems...

astNode.text: An update to Java 8 did the fix, it seems...

node.contents: Very rarely I get a deadlock while using wiki-java. Having a look at the full thread dump (acquired via kill -3 $JAVA-PID) suggests that the deadlock seems to be originating somewhere in the SSLSocketImpl. I'd prefer to avoid this deadlock in the first place (instead of doing some hacky recovery) but I am unsure how to find the cause and prevent it. Is there a way to set a timeout in the SSLSocketImpl or throw an exception in case of the deadlock? (It would be pretty straightforward to catch it in the main loop and redo the last call)
